1) Deep Learning

Your diagram contains:

Input Layer
Hidden Layer
Output Layer

Because it has hidden layers, it becomes:

Deep Learning Network
Connection
More Hidden Layers = Deep Learning

Single perceptron has no hidden layer.
This diagram has hidden neurons, so it is Deep Learning.

2) Supervised Learning

In supervised learning:

ANN gets input data
Correct output(label) is already known

Example:

Input	Correct Output
Student marks	Pass
Email text	Spam
Connection in Diagram

Input layer gives data:

0.3, 0.4, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.1

Output layer compares prediction with actual answer.

That is:

Supervised Learning
3) Loss Function

Loss function measures error for one prediction.

Example:

Predicted Output = 0.9
Actual Output = 1

Loss calculates difference.

Connection in Diagram

After feedforward:

ANN produces output
Loss function checks:
"How wrong is this output?"
4) Cost Function

Cost function is average of all losses.

Connection
Loss Function → Single prediction error
Cost Function → Overall network error

During training:

ANN reduces cost function
Accuracy improves

